@c @node Tutorial, Enigma Hints, Spoilers, Spoilers
@c @section Walkthrough for Tutorial

@c The landscapes in the ``Tutorial'' level pack are supposed to be easy.
@c Except for the last one, which is not...  This section of the manual was
@c contributed by Jacob Scott.

@c This walkthrough is for my level ``Advanced Tutorial'' in the
@c ``Tutorial'' level pack (to change level packs, click on ``Level Pack''
@c at the bottom-left of the screen and select a level pack).  While you
@c are playing, you should read all the documents in a room as soon as
@c possible.

@c The final goal for this level, as for most Enigma levels, is to find and
@c hit ``Oxyd'' stones with your black ball.  When you hit an oxyd stone, it
@c opens and shows a color.  If you hit two oxyd stones of the same color in
@c a row, they will both stay open.  Once you've matched up all pairs of
@c oxyd stones in a level, you have completed the level.

@c The level contains about twenty rooms, organized into three separate
@c areas.  In the first area, you will be encounter some of the basic
@c blocks and floor types you will see in Enigma levels and solve a couple
@c of simple puzzles.  The second area is more challenging and will
@c introduce you to a useful technique in outthinking an active enemy.  The
@c third and final area leads you to experiment with more advanced
@c interactions between Enigma objects.  In this particular level, all of
@c the oxyd stones can be found in a single room at the end of area 3.

@c @subsection Area 1

@c You start in a room surrounded by immovable walls except for a gap to
@c the right, some water near the bottom-left, and a closed gate near the
@c top-left.

@c Room 1: Go through the gap in the wall to the right.

@c Room 2: Simply avoid the blocks with pictures of skulls on them.

@c Room 3: Push the four wooden blocks into the water in the same row to
@c create a bridge to the opposite bank.  Now hit the blackish blocks to the
@c right.  Move the tan blocks out of the way (maybe to the left) and
@c bridge to the right with the two wooden blocks.

@c Room 4: Go close to the top.  When it begins to chase you, lead it to
@c the left and around the blocks in the center of the room.  Once the top
@c is far enough away from the entrance to the next room, run through.

@c Room 5: The only dangers here are the skulls near the bottom of the
@c room.  The first floor type is metal---this floor is similar to the
@c ``leaves'' floor that you have been traveling on so far.  The next floor
@c type is ``red''---it is somewhat difficult to slow down or speed up on
@c this floor.  The third floor type is ice---there is little friction on
@c this floor.  The last floor type is space---there is no friction here;
@c you can't change velocity (speed and direction) when you are on this
@c type of floor.

@c Room 6: Simply go over the slopes.  Then exit to the left by passing over
@c the ``inverse'' floor---when you are on this type of floor and you push
@c the mouse (or similar controller) in one direction, the ball speeds up
@c in the opposite direction (if you are having trouble here, try turning
@c your mouse around 180 degrees).

@c Room 7: Try to get the extra ball by putting the movable block on the
@c lower trigger.  First hit it up one square and then left six
@c squares.  Next hit it five squares down and two squares to the right.
@c Finally hit it one square up and one square to the left. Take the extra
@c ball and then put the block on the other trigger to open the gate in the
@c left wall of the room.

@c Room 8: Take the dynamite (you will have to go on the ice) and drop it
@c in front of the yellow blocks to blow them up and get past.  The spade
@c is unnecessary but you should still experiment with it.

@c Room 9: Hit the lowest movable block to the left.  Now the boulders
@c trying to go to the right are blocking your path.  Hit the rightmost
@c movable block (to the left or to the right) to let the boulders
@c past.  Take the magic wand (don't accidentally hit any boulders when
@c the magic wand is in the front of your inventory) and hit the movable
@c block above the water down.  Now go back to the right of the room, put
@c the magic wand in the front of your inventory, and hit the top three
@c boulders of the long column (try not to get run over by any
@c boulders).  Hit the leftmost movable block to the left and go into the
@c next room.

@c Room 10: Hit the switch.  Now hit the two tan blocks up (one square
@c each).  Hit the middle (from top to bottom) wooden block to the left and
@c the wooden block that used to be right above it up into the water.  Hit
@c the rest of the blocks into the water in the same column (try not to
@c drown).  Now hit the window (the blue line) with high speed.  Take the
@c ball and cross over to the bridge into the first room.  From there go
@c through the open gate.

@c @subsection Area 2

@c In area two, you will encounter a rotor, which is an active enemy of
@c your black ball.  Different rotors can act slightly differently, but they
@c are never very smart.  The way to get past it is to trick it to do what
@c you want it to do, while keeping yourself out of danger.

@c Look around this area (but don't hit the movable block yet).  You need to
@c get through the three closed gates at the top of this area.

@c First gate: Hit the white ball to the left (don't accidentally go
@c through the black one-way block) to free it (this may require a few
@c tries).  Take the spoon and hit the white ball through the white one-way
@c block hard enough so that it doesn't get stuck.  Now go through the black
@c one-way block and hit the white ball through the passageway.  Hit the
@c white ball hard enough through the next white one-way block so it
@c doesn't get stuck beneath it.  Once the white ball is through, use the
@c spoon; you restart at the beginning of the level and are no longer
@c trapped.  Go back up through the gate---the first gate near the top of
@c this room is open.

@c Second gate: Hit the movable block in the rightmost room of this area to
@c the right and run.  A document with useful information should appear in
@c the gate connecting area one and area two.  Bring the rotor (by making it
@c chase you, like you did with the top) to above the wall to the right of
@c the gate between the first two areas.  Run through the gate and go over
@c the bridge to the room below you.  Hit the switch to close the gate and
@c return to the room where you initially started.  You will no longer be
@c able to see the rotor---it won't be in the room where you will be---but
@c if you look carefully, you will be able to see where it is.  The goal
@c here is to, without exposing yourself to any danger, get the rotor to go
@c to a trigger and open a gate for you.  Get the rotor to follow you from
@c the top-right of this room to the top-left of the room.  It should be
@c pushed to the left by some slopes.  Bring the rotor down on the left
@c until it will not continue and you hear the sound of a trigger being
@c pushed.  Hit the switch to open the gate and return to area two---the
@c second gate should be open.

@c Third gate: Simply hit the movable block that the rotor started under
@c to the trigger in the room where it started.  Return to the room to your
@c left---the third gate should be open.  Go through the three open
@c gates.

@c @subsection Area 3

@c In area three you need to explore the interactions between particular
@c Enigma objects.  Here you will find lasers, mirrors, and coins.  You will
@c need to solve a simple laser-and-mirror puzzle to get a laser to hit a
@c particular stone, which will open a bridge to the next room.  To get past
@c the next few rooms, you will need to create some new objects by hitting
@c existing objects with the laser beam.

@c In the first part of this area there are three mirrors and a laser with
@c a switch.

@c Room 1: You need to get the laser to hit the black stone.  Hit the
@c bottom-left mirror down one square and orient it so that it looks like a
@c ``\'' by hitting it slowly (it should be thirty squares directly to the
@c left of the laser).  Hit the top-left mirror eight squares to the left,
@c one square down, and orient it so that it looks like a ``/'' (it should
@c be four squares directly above the previous mirror).  Hit the top-right
@c mirror two squares up and then three squares to the right (it should be
@c twenty-two squares directly to the right of the previous mirror and one
@c square below the black stone).  Put this mirror in the ``/''
@c orientation.  Now hit the switch to turn on the laser (don't get hit by
@c or roll over the laser beam).  Once it is completely up, go over the
@c bridge to your right.

@c Room 2: Take some coins and return to the previous room.  By turning off
@c and on the laser, hit one of the coins with the laser beam.  Take the
@c object produced (an umbrella), repeat the process, and take the second
@c umbrella.  Now drop one of the coins next to a mirror and hit the mirror
@c over it.  Hit this coin with a value of five with the laser beam to
@c produce a hammer.  Hit the hammer with the laser beam (by turning the
@c laser off and on) to produce a sword.  If you want some more balls, you
@c can hit mirrors over coins twice and hit the coins of increased value
@c (to ten, the highest possible) with the laser.  To return to the room
@c with the knights, put the mirrors back in their initial positions,
@c remove all objects blocking the laser, and hit the switch.  Now use the
@c right mouse button or the ``tab'' key to get the sword in the front
@c (left) of your inventory.  Hit some of the knights (four times each) to
@c get past.

@c Room 3: Use an umbrella and travel over the abyss to the room below you
@c and then into the room to your right.  If the ring surrounding you begins
@c to blink, use another umbrella.

@c Room 4: Simply match the oxyd stones by hitting oxyds of the same colors
@c as the activated oxyd stones (one at a time).  Don't hit the fart
@c stones (the black stones).  You win!


